# 🧠 Concepts Learned

## Virtual Machine

A Virtual Machine (VM) is software that allows multiple operating systems to run on a single physical computer.

---

## Ubuntu

Ubuntu is a Linux distribution widely used for servers, cloud computing, networking, and cybersecurity.

---

## Terminal

The Terminal is a command-line interface (CLI) that allows users to interact with the Linux operating system using commands.

---

## sudo

`sudo` allows a user to execute commands with administrator (root) privileges.

---

## apt

`apt` is Ubuntu's package manager used to install, update, and remove software packages.

